body:
@mkoch1 
Could you squash commits into one if you don't mind? I know it's more than 2000 lines change but looks like separating commits are not needed.
And I would like to wait for 1.1.0 RC vote to pass to avoid any conflicts with the release. That says, this is not going to be included to 1.1.0.

@alexlehm 
The updated explanation looks good. 
Please split commit message by title and body, and leave only abstraction for the change. You can rebase or amend the commit and force push.

@srdo 
Yes agreed that it will still lots of log messages there... Need to throttle even with debug level.
Btw, adding log message to ISpoutWaitStrategy doesn't help for resolving STORM-2384 since it doesn't know why there's empty emit. It's even called when nextTuple doesn't emit normally.

@aandis Could you implement `throttling log message` with removing **duplicated** log messages for given period (say N secs)?
